# Vendored on-device watermark ONNX models (tens of MB each) — Andy-run, never
# generated by a normal build. Adobe TrustMark decoders are downloaded by
# scripts/fetch-trustmark-models.ts (needs network); the Meta Content Seal
# (Pixel Seal) extractor is converted by scripts/convert-contentseal-onnx.py
# (needs torch + the videoseal checkpoint). Not committed for the same reason
# node_modules/ isn't: too large for git, and re-producible from a documented
# source. The web shell fetches each once at runtime and caches the bytes in
# IndexedDB (see shells/web/src/lib/{trustmark,contentseal}.ts), so end users
# never touch this directory.
public/models/
# Same story for the onnxruntime-web wasm/mjs runtime the models run on —
# copied from node_modules/onnxruntime-web/dist/ per fetch-trustmark-models.ts
# (trustmark.ts sets ort.env.wasm.wasmPaths = '/ort/').
public/ort/

# Claude Code local state (worktrees etc.) — never commit
.claude/
